e heard the term Namakura being translated as sort of like a dull or blunt sword with a pathetic cutting edge. I haven't found a very precise or very good translation on what a Namakura really is.<br>
In the novel I'm writing, you see, I have a character that wields one of these. He says, &quot;My Namakura. I had it's cutting edge to be dulled to the point that it cannot cut flesh.&quot; So he purposely has a blunt sword which does not allow him to kill people (sort of like Kenshin's sakabatou, but not exactly.) Would this be almost right? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maimaipanda>maimaipanda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Resident Panda</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/18/03 8:48:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1098.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sit.wisc.edu/~mamiller2/temp/pandatea.jpg height=146 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Namakura</span><hr size=1> Hmm... 'namakura' basically just means dull or not sharp.  But I'm not so sure it would have an implication of &quot;pathetic&quot; ...  it's just a regular adjective.  <br>
<br>
You can use it in much the same way as we do in the states - for instance &quot;kare ha namakura no otoko&quot; = &quot;he is a dull (guy/person)&quot;.  But it is most generally used for knives and swords.<br>
<br>
I asked a couple of japanese friends and they both agreed that &quot;namakura&quot; doesn't have any special connotations as far as representing a particular type of dull sword (i.e like a practice sword designed not to cut flesh). <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">Mamonaku. 11ban sen ni  Panda densha ga mairimasu. </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">Abunai desu kara, kiiro no sen no uchigawa made osagarikudasai.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><br>
Ueno! Ueno! Owasuremono ga nai you ni gochuui kudasai!</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
